text:
The root cause of this bug does indeed appear to be specific to the FreeBSD port of Gitolite so I've reopened this bug.

The patch file that leads to the bug is only in the FreeBSD port and can be found here: https://cgit.freebsd.org/ports/tree/devel/gitolite/files/patch-src_triggers_post-compile_ssh-authkeys

Lines 30-32 of the patch are the regex modification that causes ecdsa-sk and and ed25519-sk keys to be treated as options instead of key types. Those lines are copied below for reference:

-    return "command=\"$glshell $user" . ( $kfn ? " $f" : "" ) . "\",$auth_options $line[0]";
+    return "command=\"$glshell $user" . ( $kfn ? " $f" : "" ) . "\",$auth_options" .
+        ($line[0] =~ /^(ecdsa|ssh)-/ ? " " : "," ) . $line[0];
